# AI Agent Development Rules

## Overview

Agents live in `app/agents/`. The primary model is Anthropic Claude via AWS Bedrock. LangChain is the abstraction layer. Agents use tools to interact with Excel files and the database.

---

## Philosophy

- **Tool-calling agents**: Agents use LangChain's `create_tool_calling_agent` to build tool-calling executors
- **Status callbacks**: Agents can emit status updates during execution
- **Closure pattern**: Tools capture instance state via `tools_self = self`
- **Validation loop**: Planner and Validator work together iteratively

---

## Project Structure

```
app/
├── agents/                # AI agent implementations
│   ├── base_agent.py      # BaseAgent + BaseToolCallingAgent
│   ├── constraint_analyzer.py  # Parses Hebrew constraints
│   ├── shift_planner.py   # Creates shift assignments
│   └── validator.py       # Validates plans
├── tools/                 # Tool classes with get_tools() pattern
│   ├── log_tools.py       # log_thought
│   ├── excel_tools.py     # Excel manipulation
│   └── constraint_tools.py # Constraint parsing
├── prompts/               # System prompts as constants
├── dal/                   # Data Access Layer (SQLAlchemy)
└── agent_websocket/       # WebSocket server (FastAPI)
```

